<br>
I wasn't sure where I should put this post because it is related to roleplay, but I'm asking about RL information from a medical stand point.  (Or well, I suppose I'm asking more of your approval from a fantasy roleplaying stand point.) I decided to place it here, but if you wish to move it to a more suitable forum, then by all means, do so!  But anyhow, I'll get to the point...but first a small bit of background.<br>
<br>
For awhile, I've been trying to piece together a RP persona and background for one of my main characters on Xev.  I attempted to create him here, but his personality was just too complicated for me to roleplay on my first try, so I used an easier personality for him here.  But now I want to make another attempt at getting him together because I am comtemplating joining Last Exodus, a roleplaying guild on Xev that you may or may not have heard of.  But anyhow, being the perfectionist that I am, I want to get out all the kinks from my characters background and persona before launching into it. <br>
<br>
So anyhow, the back bone to both his personality and his past is the scar he carries on his hand. (I think I will make it his left hand)  The scar goes diagonally (down and to the right if I make it on the left hand) across the center of his palm, and I think I'm going to make it about 2 inchs long. It will (sort of) follow his &quot;life line,&quot; if you know which crease that is on the palm.  He receives this scar when his father pierces through the back of his hand with a sword of some type.  At the time his hand is resting upon his brothers chest, so it is relaxed and slightly curved to his brothers body.  If you need more specifics on the scenario in order to answer my question (I am almost there, I promise, I'm just longwinded), then simply post and for them for I will gladly give them.  But anyhow, from a medical stand point or perhaps just a simple fantasy roleplaying stand point, would it be possible for his hand to heal without any disformities aside from a scar?  Because piercing through his hand would mean cutting through any blood vessels in the area, and snapping through the finger bones on the inside on the palm.  I'm trying to think of it from a fantasy stand point, like, he used &quot;Lay of Hands&quot; on himself afterwards since he was a low level paladin at the time, though I was planning for him to use it on his brother.  Or perhaps he stumbled to the cleric guild just after the event and a cleric is able to mend his hand, while leave only a scar?  <br>
<br>
Anyhow...I guess I asking more for all your approval of this.  I figured all roleplay professionals would be the best people to bring my question to.  So anyhow, if you could please let me know whether or not you think that my whole idea from his scar is acceptable by the laws and standards of Everquest, or even from a medical RL view, it would be much appreciated!  Anyhow, I want to thank you in advance for what ever help you may be able to give a novice roleplayer like myself!  And I'm sorry for how long this post was - I am notoriously long winded, so I hope you can forgive me!   <br>
